{"title_page": "The Military Man", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Military Man\n| film name      = Le Militaire\n| image          = Le militaire.jpg\n| caption        =\n| director       = [[No\u00ebl Mitrani]]\n| writer         = No\u00ebl Mitrani\n| starring       = [[Laurent Lucas]]<br>[[No\u00e9mie Godin-Vigneau]]\n| cinematography = [[Bruno Philip]]\n| music          = [[James Gelfand]]\n| editing        = [[Arthur Tarnowski]]\n| runtime        = 79 minutes\n| released       = {{Film date|2014|10|15|df=y}}\n| budget         =\n| country        = Canada\n| language       = French\n}}\n'''''The Military Man''''' ({{lang-fr|Le Militaire}}) is a 2014 Canadian drama film starring [[Laurent Lucas]], written and directed by [[No\u00ebl Mitrani]].\n\n== Plot ==\nA former French soldier lives in solitude in Montreal. Since returning from Afghanistan with a leg injury, this soldier has had trouble coming to grips with reality and overcoming his loneliness. The trauma caused by his memories of the conflict leads him towards an unhealthy relationship with women. One day, his behavior brings him into contact with a woman and makes him questions his motives.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Laurent Lucas]] ... as Bertrand\n* [[No\u00e9mie Godin Vigneau]] ... as Audrey\n* [[Larry Day]]\n* [[Harry Standjofski]]\n\n==Production==\n'''''Le Militaire''''' (The Military Man) is an independent feature film shot on [[super 16 mm]] like a [[documentary]]. For the role, [[Laurent Lucas]] specially grew his beard and shaved his head. The film has been shot on location in [[Montreal]] with a very small crew.\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|3775978|Le Militaire}}\n* {{YouTube|LoamXcIRi28|Trailer}} \n* FNC (Review) [http://nouveaucinema.ca/#/2014/programme/long-metrage/141/10641]\n* Review (French) [http://www.filmsquebec.com/films/militaire-noel-mitrani/]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Military Man, The}}\n[[Category:2014 films]]\n[[Category:Canadian films]]\n[[Category:French-language 